<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFB96A06F7EF9FA917E7B1E4" pageId="66" pageNumber="824" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFB96A06F7EF9FA917E7B1E4" blockId="66.[2065,2660,2426,2853]" pageId="66" pageNumber="824">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFB96A06F7449FA9172EB123" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[2232,2350,2544,2577]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Laephotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="824" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Laephotis</taxonomicName>
appears to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFB96A06F7599C41179EB10B" baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[2213,2462,2584,2617]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="824" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">Neoromicia capensis</taxonomicName>
based on limited genetic data, making 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFB96A06F6769C191413B153" box="[2442,2579,2624,2657]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="824" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neoromicia</taxonomicName>
paraphyletic since 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFB96A06F72A9C3E174DB1BA" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[2262,2381,2663,2696]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Laephotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="824" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Laephotis</taxonomicName>
is embedded within it. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFB96A06F7C29CD7174EB19D" authorityName="Setzer" authorityYear="1971" box="[2110,2382,2702,2735]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Laephotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="824" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="namibensis">Laephotis namibensis</taxonomicName>
might be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFB96A06F7459CEC173EB1E4" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[2233,2366,2741,2774]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Laephotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="824" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wintoni">L. wintoni</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFB96A06F7EF9C871697B07C" pageId="66" pageNumber="824" type="distribution">
<caption id="90EB6676FFB96A06F7EF9C871697B07C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398055" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398055" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398055/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="824" targetBox="[1451,2043,2438,2853]" targetPageId="66">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFB96A06F7EF9C871697B07C" blockId="66.[2065,2660,2426,2853]" lastBlockId="66.[1453,2660,2861,3486]" pageId="66" pageNumber="824">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFB96A06F7EF9C8716C3B1CD" bold="true" box="[2067,2243,2782,2815]" pageId="66" pageNumber="824">Distribution.</emphasis>
Disjunct distribution, from C 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB96A06F7C99D5D16ADB017" box="[2101,2221,2820,2853]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="66" pageNumber="824">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
S through parts of 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB96A06F6309D5D1421B017" box="[2508,2593,2820,2853]" name="Kenya" pageId="66" pageNumber="824">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB96A06FA519D74182CB07C" box="[1453,1580,2861,2894]" name="Tanzania" pageId="66" pageNumber="824">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
to S 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB96A06F9889D7418DCB07C" box="[1652,1756,2861,2894]" name="Zambia" pageId="66" pageNumber="824">Zambia</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB96A06F8F79D74197CB07C" box="[1803,1916,2861,2894]" name="Lesotho" pageId="66" pageNumber="824">Lesotho</collectingCountry>
and E 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB96A06F81E9D741693B07C" box="[2018,2195,2861,2894]" name="South Africa" pageId="66" pageNumber="824">South Africa</collectingCountry>
.
